# Java Input and Data Type Operations

## Description
This simple Java program demonstrates how to:
- Read different data types using the Scanner class
- Perform basic operations on integers, floats, characters, booleans, and strings

## Features
- Input:
  - Two integers
  - One floating-point number
  - One character
  - One boolean value
  - User's name (string)
- Output:
  - Sum, difference, and product of integers
  - Floating-point number multiplied by 2
  - Next character in ASCII
  - Opposite boolean value
  - Greeting message

